I tried doing a a simple profile java application using the tptp 1009 build and I receieved the error in the summary.

Here are the steps I used

Here are my steps. 
            install fresh 3.2.1 eclipse 
            unzip emf 
            unzip tptp 1009 runtime and sdk 
  
Create new workspace. 
            click on Profile ? button 
            clink on new ?Java Application? 
  
Brings up dialog box saying 
            Plugin org.eclipse.hyades.trace.ui cannot load class 
                        org.eclipse.hyades.trace.ui.internal.launcher.ProfileJavaApplicationTabGroup 

I tried the identical steps in 4.2.1 and everything worked.

This test was on win ia32.

Does you driver path contain space? eg. "C:\Documents and Settings\user\Desktop". Can you try rerun with driver locate at a path with no space?

I suspect this is a dup of 161276.

Yes... My eclipse is under Documents and Settings...

I copied it to C:\eclipse.3.2.1 and my Profile launch configuration comes up.

Looks like you are correct!

Thanks for the prompt reply!

Regards,

Kevin
